.SH "NAME"
ccnsyncwatch \- watch sync operations and report new content objects
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.sp
\fBccnsyncwatch\fR [\fB\-h\fR] [\fB\-t\fR \fItopo\-uri\fR] [\fB\-p\fR \fIprefix\-uri\fR] [\fB\-f\fR \fIfilter\-uri\fR] [\fB\-r\fR \fIroothash\-hex\fR] [\fB\-w\fR \fItimeout\-secs\fR]
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.sp
The \fBccnsyncwatch\fR program is for monitoring the operation of the sync agent of a repository, and the source provides an example of how to use the sync library interface\&.
.SH "OPTIONS"
.PP
\fB\-h\fR
.RS 4
Print usage information and exit\&.
.RE
.PP
\fB\-t\fR \fItopo\-uri\fR
.RS 4
Specify the CCNx URI representing the prefix under which Sync agents communicate\&.
.RE
.PP
\fB\-p\fR \fIprefix\-uri\fR
.RS 4
Specify the CCNx URI representing the prefix of the information which the Sync agents are exchanging\&.
.RE
.PP
\fB\-f\fR \fIfilter\-uri\fR
.RS 4
This option may occur multiple times\&. Order is significant and should match the order used when the Sync configuration slice was defined\&. Provides zero or more CCNx URIs representing filter clauses, see
\fBccnsyncslice\fR(1) for further information\&.
.RE
.PP
\fB\-r\fR \fIroothash\-hex\fR
.RS 4
If present, indicates that the differences noted should be from the current root hash (\fIroothash\-hex\fR
is the empty string) or a particular root hash (an even number of hex digits) previously noted in a Sync exchange\&. It is an error to provide a root hash that is not a valid hash for the slice being monitored\&.
.RE
.PP
\fB\-w\fR \fItimeout\-secs\fR
.RS 4
The time in seconds that sync activity should be monitored, or \-1 to run until interrupted\&.
.RE
